sciences, with different approaches to mediatization of communication. The chapters span from how mediatization meets climate change and contribute to globalization to questions on life and death in mediatized settings. The book deals with mass media as well as communication with networked, digital media. The topic of this volume makes a valuable contribution to the understanding of contemporary processes of social, cultural and political changes. The handbook provides the reader with the most current state of mediatization research.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCommunicationxSocial aspects. 0aMass mediaxSocial aspects. 0aSocial change. 0aSocial interaction. 4aMediatization. 4aMedien. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Communication Studies.2bisacsh  aMediatization, Media, Mediated Communication.1 aAsp, Kent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAuslander, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAverbeck-Lietz, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBogoch, Bryna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBolin, Göran, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCouldry, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEss, Charles M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEsser, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFigenschou, Tine Ustad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFinnemann, Niels Ole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFornäs, Johan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrandsen, Kirsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.g